README: Draco bash environment dotfiles
================================================================================
- Note: Most of the files in this directory are dotfiles.  You must 'ls -a' to
  see them.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Recommended use of these scripts:

1. Create ~/.bash_profile based on the provided 'sample.bash_profile' template.
   a. You MUST set the value of DRACO_ENV_DIR to point to your draco location.
   b. You can add your own prompt, aliases, functions and modules to the
      INTERACTIVE section.  Some of these are provided in the
      sample.bash_profile, but are commented out.
2. Create ~/.bashrc based on the provided 'sample.bashrc' template.
   a. You can add your own customizations for non-login shells.
